1
00:01:42,940 --> 00:01:44,640
不到20%的人愿意看到
Less than 20% are comfortable

2
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:47,510
总统和副总统有任何亲属关系
with a president and a vice president being related in any way.

3
00:01:47,510 --> 00:01:50,900
不到10%的人支持从未当选过公职的人
Less than 10% approve of someone who's never held elected office.

4
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,430
但如果我们能扭转局面呢
But if we can move the needle... 

5
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:53,580
提升40个百分点吗
Forty points?

6
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:54,460
要看我们怎么说
It's how we frame it.

7
00:01:54,460 --> 00:01:56,980
她的支持率不错  比我还高
Her favorables are decent. They're better than mine.

8
00:01:57,050 --> 00:01:59,870
是对人不对事  就她作为联合国大使而言
In a void, but when it comes to her time as the UN ambassador,

9
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:00,770
支持率就猛跌了
they fall off a cliff.

10
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:03,050
表现和经验是重要因素
Performance and experience are big factors.

11
00:02:03,050 --> 00:02:05,910
那我们得强调她的优点而非软肋
Then we have to amplify her strengths, not her weaknesses.

12
00:02:05,910 --> 00:02:07,610
我们需要一个有价值的副总统
We're looking for a VP who's an asset.

13
00:02:07,610 --> 00:02:09,260
而这项研究表明她不是
This research proves she isn't.

14
00:02:09,260 --> 00:02:12,760
你的工作不是劝我放弃  而是想办法说服大家
Your job is not to dissuade me, but to figure out how we sell it.

15
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:15,500
先生  可选的人很多
Sir, there are so many people to choose from.

16
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:16,490
如果目标是获选
If the goal is to win,

17
00:02:16,490 --> 00:02:18,490
-我们在不遗余力  -赛斯
- and we're bending over backwards-- -Seth.

18
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,190
总统要我们制定计划
The president asked us to develop a plan,

19
00:02:21,190 --> 00:02:22,630
那我们就制定计划
so that's what we'll do.

20
00:02:25,750 --> 00:02:27,130
去我办公室等我
I'll meet you in my office.

21
00:02:35,970 --> 00:02:38,120
-您知道他是对的  -当然了
- You know he's right. - Well, of course he's right.

22
00:02:39,630 --> 00:02:41,450
或许我们可以给她点别的
Maybe we offer something else.

23
00:02:42,570 --> 00:02:43,890
她不会听的
She won't listen.

24
00:02:47,790 --> 00:02:49,020
莉安呢
What about LeAnn?

25
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,250
我也在考虑那个
Yes, I was thinking that, too.

26
00:02:53,570 --> 00:02:55,490
问题是怎么让她配合
Question is how to co-opt her.

27
00:02:56,780 --> 00:02:57,870
她喜欢支票
She likes paychecks.

28
00:02:57,870 --> 00:03:01,050
不  光钱不行  她想要政治影响力
No, it's gotta be more than money. She wants coattails.

29
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:08,040
我跟克莱尔交换
We swap Claire's for mine.

30
00:03:08,660 --> 00:03:11,610
-竞选经理吗  -我们需要新鲜血液
- Campaign manager? - We could use some fresh blood.

31
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:13,640
这我同意  但莉安
That I agree with, but LeAnn?

32
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:15,170
没法保证我们能控制她
I mean, there's no guarantee that we can control her.

33
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:17,000
但如果她能说服克莱尔改主意
Yeah, but if she can convince Claire to change her mind,

34
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,560
那对我就足够了
that's all I need. 

35
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:21,030
是
Yes.

36
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:22,740
战况室都等您了  先生
They're ready for you in the Situation Room, sir.

37
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:23,990
我就过去
I'll be right there.

38
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:26,540
如果有必要你可以跟她合作
You could work with her if you had to.

39
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:28,860
我不非得喜欢她才能跟她合作
I don't have to like her to work with her.

40
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:31,670
-很好  打电话吧  -您还想让赛斯知情吗
- Good, make the call. - You still want Seth on the plan?

41
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:34,760
是的  直到莉安同意  我需要担心他吗
Yes, until LeAnn's on board. Do I have to worry about him?

42
00:03:34,770 --> 00:03:37,870
我们挖得很深  他的电邮和手机记录里没查到
We dug pretty deep. Nothing in his emails or phone records.

43
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:39,950
他聪明  知道掩盖踪迹
He's smart enough to cover his tracks.

44
00:03:40,650 --> 00:03:41,950
我去跟他谈谈
I'll talk to him.

45
00:04:03,180 --> 00:04:06,640
-你觉得这幅画如何  -我不知道
- What do you think of this painting? - I'm not sure.

46
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:12,540
沃克和我有一晚曾坐在这里  盯着这幅画看
Walker and I sat here one night, stared up at a painting,

47
00:04:13,330 --> 00:04:14,790
现在挂在总统办公室的那副蓝色的
the blue one that's in the Oval now. 

48
00:04:14,790 --> 00:04:16,600
他们换上了这副
They replaced it with this.

49
00:04:17,270 --> 00:04:18,670
那不是美国国旗
That's not the American flag.

50
00:04:18,670 --> 00:04:21,680
不  是南军的旗
No, it's the rebel flag... 

51
00:04:21,810 --> 00:04:24,040
沉入虚无
sinking into oblivion.

52
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,830
那是闪电吗
Is that a lightning bolt?

53
00:04:28,340 --> 00:04:29,850
我以为是的...
Oh, I assume...

54
00:04:34,590 --> 00:04:38,830
除非是想把船画成独角兽还没画好
Unless it's just a bad attempt at making the ship a unicorn.

55
00:04:38,830 --> 00:04:39,960
你看出来了吗
Do you see that?

56
00:04:40,610 --> 00:04:42,010
色彩不错
Colors are nice.

57
00:04:42,410 --> 00:04:43,820
我真不喜欢
I hate it.

58
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,310
那我也不喜欢
I guess I hate it, too.

59
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,850
我想在白宫
I suppose it's not a good idea to have

60
00:04:49,850 --> 00:04:52,020
挂联邦旗大概不是个好主意
the Confederate flag hanging here in the White House

61
00:04:52,020 --> 00:04:55,300
尤其经历了南卡的事
after everything that's happened in South Carolina.

62
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:57,060
虽然它是在下沉
Even if it is sinking.

63
00:04:58,540 --> 00:05:00,040
你觉得我们该挂什么
What do you think we should put up?

64
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,150
我不知道  您更喜欢的东西
I don't know. Something you like better.

65
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:09,780
你带那支我签字的马克笔了吗
Do you have that marker I sign things with?

66
00:05:17,630 --> 00:05:19,220
把你的手放在墙上
Put your hand up on the wall.

67
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,630
-先生  -放在墙上
- Sir? - Put it on the wall.

68
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,690
手指伸开一点
Spread your fingers a little bit.

69
00:05:46,770 --> 00:05:48,680
等等  好了
Wait. Okay.

70
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:54,920
嗯  今天玩到这儿吧
Yeah... That's enough fun for today. -

71
00:06:02,410 --> 00:06:06,150
道格  我不知道该怎么做到他要我做的事
Doug, I don't know how to do what he's asking me to do.

72
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:08,560
-没有魔法...  -泄露事件
- There is not some magical-- - The leaks.

73
00:06:10,170 --> 00:06:13,480
-是你吗  -你认真的吗
- Was it you? - Are you serious?

74
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:14,660
非常认真
Very.

75
00:06:15,130 --> 00:06:18,460
我像其他人一样上交了我的通讯
I handed over all of my correspondence, just like everyone else.

76
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:20,140
那不能证明什么
Doesn't prove anything.

77
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:22,830
我是在挽救他的竞选
I'm trying to save this campaign.

78
00:06:23,370 --> 00:06:25,650
如果我想搞破坏  让总统自己来就好
If I wanted to sabotage it, I'd let the president do it himself,

79
00:06:25,650 --> 00:06:27,750
而不是在副总统的事上跟他对着干
instead of fighting back on this VP thing.

80
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,010
或许那只是装样子
Or that's just a cover.

81
00:06:29,010 --> 00:06:31,450
去年你不在的时候
I've been in the trenches for the past year

82
00:06:31,850 --> 00:06:34,520
我一直在第一线  现在你还怀疑我
while you've been gone, and now you doubt me?

83
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,300
我不需要这套
I don't need this.

84
00:06:36,710 --> 00:06:39,040
你得到这份工作是靠挖丑事
You got this job by digging up dirt.

85
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:41,880
如果你到现在还不信任我
If you can't trust me by now, 

86
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:44,250
我不知道我还在这儿干吗
I don't know what I'm doing here.

87
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:46,410
你是说你想辞职吗
Are you saying you wanna resign?

88
00:06:46,410 --> 00:06:48,380
那是我最不想的了
That is the last thing that I want,

89
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:51,290
但你没有给我留下的动力
but you're not giving me any incentive to stay.

90
00:06:56,310 --> 00:06:59,110
好吧  去它的
All right. Fuck it.

91
00:07:03,010 --> 00:07:06,540
赛斯  我现在选择信任你
Seth, I'm choosing to believe you right now,

92
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:08,860
但如果我有一日感到后悔了
but if I come to regret that decision--

93
00:07:08,860 --> 00:07:11,280
你不会的  因为不是我干的
You won't, because it's not me.

94
00:07:11,810 --> 00:07:13,220
我还是认为密查姆有可能
I still think it could be Meechum.

95
00:07:13,230 --> 00:07:14,350
不是他
It wasn't.

96
00:07:14,650 --> 00:07:16,470
-你确定  -完全确定
- You're sure? - I'm positive.

97
00:07:16,730 --> 00:07:18,250
总统也确定
And so is the president.

98
00:07:19,670 --> 00:07:20,980
我可以走了吗
May I go?

99
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:24,030
还是你想谈谈第一夫人的计划
Or did you want to discuss the plan for the First Lady?

100
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:27,500
我要打电话  我稍后去你办公室
I have some calls to make. I'll come to your office after.

101
00:07:36,130 --> 00:07:37,520
给我接莉安·哈维
Get me LeAnn Harvey.

102
00:07:38,690 --> 00:07:41,680
米尔金将住在他家  安东·考斯基
Milkin will be staying with this man, Anton Khalski.

103
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,750
他原本拥有俄国
He owned the second-largest

104
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:46,190
第二大的银行  直到2013年被佩特罗夫查抄
bank in Russia until Petrov seized it in 2013.

105
00:07:46,710 --> 00:07:49,280
考斯基逃出国境去了爱沙尼亚
Khalski fled across the border to Estonia.

106
00:07:49,410 --> 00:07:52,510
我们让米尔金的飞机飞往首都塔林
We'll have Milkin's plane fly to Tallinn,

107
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:56,460
然后他会乘船去萨拉马考斯基的夏季别墅
then he'll travel by boat to Khalski's summer house on Saaremaa.

108
00:07:56,460 --> 00:07:59,460
明天  我们将结冻米尔金的美国财产
Tomorrow we'll unfreeze Milkin's American assets

109
00:07:59,570 --> 00:08:01,900
并转移到考斯基的瑞士账户
and transfer them to Khalski's Swiss accounts.

110
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:04,350
考斯基会联络他的俄国军队朋友
Khalski will reach out to his Russian military friends

111
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,100
然后开始收买他们
and then start buying them off.

112
00:08:06,100 --> 00:08:08,110
俄联邦安全局在监控考斯基吗
Are the FSB monitoring Khalski?

113
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:10,300
密切监控  他们会知道是我们在支持他
Closely. They'll know we're behind this.

114
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:12,620
-莫斯科如果质问我们呢  -当然是否认
- When Moscow confronts us? - We'll deny, of course.

115
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:14,710
如果佩特罗夫反应过激  我们是否有所准备
Are we prepared if Petrov overreacts?

116
00:08:14,710 --> 00:08:17,510
第六舰队在博斯普鲁斯海峡附近有部属
The Sixth Fleet has a presence near the Bosphorus,

117
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,130
我们在北海也有巡航
we have patrols in the North Sea.

118
00:08:19,130 --> 00:08:21,130
-起草命令吧  -先生  可以说一句吗
- Draft the order. - Sir, if I may?

119
00:08:21,130 --> 00:08:22,290
-我们讨论过了  凯茜  -是的  先生
- Yeah, we've discussed this, Cathy. - Yes, sir.

120
00:08:22,290 --> 00:08:23,960
我觉得我必须
I feel obligated

121
00:08:23,960 --> 00:08:27,200
要提出强烈的反对  这将给我们带来的外交影响
to raise my very strong objections. The diplomatic cost to us--

122
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,360
如果外交好用
If diplomacy were working,

123
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:30,980
我们根本就不需要考虑这么做了  是吧
we wouldn't have to consider this course of action, would we?

124
00:08:32,620 --> 00:08:35,190
-我已经提出了担忧  -谢谢大家
- I've voiced my concerns. - Thank you, everyone.

125
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:44,390
你不会突然让
You're not going to surprise me

126
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:46,520
总统接电话打我个措手不及吧
by putting the president on, are you?

127
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:49,320
不  只有我们  但他告诉我了
No, it's just us. He filled me in, though,

128
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,750
-关于第一夫人的要求  -怎么样
- on the First Lady's request. - And?

129
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:54,350
我们想让你当竞选经理
We wanna make you campaign manager.

130
00:08:55,380 --> 00:08:56,580
看你的邮件
Look at your email.

131
00:09:00,930 --> 00:09:03,100
-是什么  -我们的调研
- What is this? - Our research.

132
00:09:03,570 --> 00:09:05,430
结果是一样的
It all boils down to the same thing.

133
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:07,690
你们做了几个民调  又如何
You ran a few polls, so what?

134
00:09:07,690 --> 00:09:10,430
-还有焦点小组  -毫无意义
- Focus groups, too. - Meaningless.

135
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:11,910
这么低的数字可不是毫无意义
Not these numbers.

136
00:09:12,110 --> 00:09:14,380
克莱尔不能参选  你很清楚
Claire can't be on the ticket. You know she can't.

137
00:09:14,450 --> 00:09:17,750
这事不是孤立的
This isn't something you can isolate on its own.

138
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:19,920
如果油价飙升至6美元/加仑  你们就完了
If gas prices hit $6 a gallon, you're fucked.

139
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:22,350
-你们会失去所有关键人群  -我们很清楚
- You lose every key demo. - We're well aware.

140
00:09:22,370 --> 00:09:25,120
但如果总统让克莱尔做他的竞选伙伴
But if the president makes Claire his running mate,

141
00:09:25,220 --> 00:09:28,560
那么话题会转向策略而非经济
it makes the conversation tactical instead of economic.

142
00:09:28,610 --> 00:09:31,320
这就给了你们时间处理俄国危机
That buys you time on the Russia crisis.

143
00:09:31,450 --> 00:09:33,280
你们解决了那事  对总统在自信
You solve that, confidence in the president

144
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:35,400
就能转变成对总统选择的自信
translates into confidence in his choice--

145
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:39,300
我打给你不是想听你游说  我打来是想给你份工作
I didn't call you to be convinced. I called to offer you a job.

146
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:43,450
-是为了拆安德伍德夫人的台  -不仅是因为她
- Only to get to Mrs. Underwood. -This isn't just about her.

147
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:48,220
我们需要你  你能扭转竞选局势
We need you. You'll turn this campaign around.

148
00:09:48,450 --> 00:09:51,010
我好惊讶  道格  我以为你不怎么喜欢我呢
I'm surprised, Doug. I didn't think you were very fond of me.

149
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:54,430
我喜欢人才  总统也是
I'm fond of talent. So is the president.

150
00:09:55,220 --> 00:09:57,230
我忠于第一夫人
My loyalty is to the First Lady.

151
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:59,500
我只求你跟她谈谈
All I'm asking is that you talk to her.

152
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,800
这样吧  如果你把我的调查给总统看
I'll tell you what. I'll show Claire your research

153
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,570
我就把你的调查给克莱尔看
if you show the president mine.

154
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,370
这我可以同意
I can agree to that.

155
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:09,510
我根本不该跟你说话的  海瑟
I shouldn't even be talking to you, Heather.

156
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:11,790
我非常担忧有滥用职权的现象
I'm seriously concerned that there's been an abuse of power.

157
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:15,150
司法部长女士  斯坦普先生可以见您了
Madam Attorney General? Mr. Stamper, um, is ready to see you now.

158
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,330
我就去
I'll be right there.

159
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:18,990
我得挂了
I gotta go.

160
00:10:18,990 --> 00:10:20,580
负责行动的探员
The agent in charge of the operation

161
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:23,200
事后马上得到了晋升
got a promotion directly after.

162
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,000
-听着  -玛莎  如果总统
- Listen-- - Martha, if the president,

163
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,190
或他的手下  如果有人强迫联调局
or one of his staff... If anyone strong-armed the bureau

164
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,110
追查卢卡斯·古德温
into pursuing Lucas Goodwin,

165
00:10:30,230 --> 00:10:32,440
那你知道  那就是滥用职权
then you know that's an abuse of power.

166
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,060
我就为总统工作
I work for the president.

167
00:10:34,060 --> 00:10:36,510
我正要跟他的幕僚长面谈
I am about to sit down with his Chief of Staff.

168
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:39,540
-法律就是法律  -这是政治  不是法律
- The law is the law. - This is politics, not the law.

169
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:41,050
不对  你让我担任
Not true. You brought me on

170
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:43,340
副检察长是因为我正直
as solicitor general because of my integrity.

171
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:45,420
而我来找你  是因为你也一样
I am bringing this to you because of yours.

172
00:10:45,420 --> 00:10:46,720
司法部长女士
Madam Attorney General.

173
00:10:49,090 --> 00:10:50,210
我真的得挂了
I really need to go.

174
00:10:50,210 --> 00:10:52,900
如果古德温的故事有一丝真实性
If a sliver of Goodwin's story holds up...

175
00:10:52,910 --> 00:10:54,250
你怎么知道的
How did you even find this?

176
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:56,230
你的对手研究团队联络过证人保护计划的人吗
Did your oppo team speak to someone in WITSEC?

177
00:10:56,230 --> 00:10:59,610
如果是那样  这种违法行为...
Because if that's the case, then that sort of breach is not--

178
00:10:59,610 --> 00:11:03,730
-我跟他本人谈过  -什么
- I spoke to him myself, personally. - You what?

179
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:07,610
他来找我的  他找到了我
He came to me. He tracked me down.

180
00:11:08,020 --> 00:11:09,600
我不要沾这事  海瑟
I'm not touching this, Heather.

181
00:11:10,620 --> 00:11:12,460
道格  真是抱歉
Doug, sorry about that.

182
00:11:12,830 --> 00:11:14,380
-没事  -我刚刚在跟首席法官通话
- No-- - I was just on with the Chief Justice.

183
00:11:14,390 --> 00:11:16,110
-没事的  快进来吧  -谢谢
- Don't be silly, come on in. - Thank you.

184
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:17,720
-这边请  -谢谢你
- This way. - Thanks so much.

185
00:11:22,330 --> 00:11:24,420
我不知道  她作为大使时表现可不怎么样
I don't know. She didn't do that well as ambassador.

186
00:11:24,420 --> 00:11:26,050
经验不够
She wasn't experienced enough.

187
00:11:26,050 --> 00:11:27,740
等等  她做过大使
Hold on, she was an ambassador? 

188
00:11:27,740 --> 00:11:30,760
-联合国大使  -克里斯  你不看新闻吗
- At the United Nations. - Chris, don't you watch the news?

189
00:11:31,210 --> 00:11:32,690
你们多少人也有同感
How many of you feel the same?

190
00:11:35,110 --> 00:11:38,470
除了缺乏经验  有其他原因吗
Any other reasons, besides lack of experience?

191
00:11:38,470 --> 00:11:41,600
她在莫斯科情绪失控时很冲动
Well, she was really impulsive when she had that outburst in Moscow.

192
00:11:41,850 --> 00:11:43,650
她根本就不该去
Well, she never should've been there in the first place.

193
00:11:43,650 --> 00:11:45,820
参议院都否决了她
I mean, the Senate voted her down,

194
00:11:45,820 --> 00:11:47,340
她丈夫还是任命了她
and then her husband just appoints her?

195
00:11:47,340 --> 00:11:48,640
哪能这样
That's not right.

196
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:52,160
瞧  我喜欢她这个人  但我同意
Okay, see, I like her as a person, but I agree,

197
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:53,970
她该继续做她的第一夫人
she should stick to being First Lady.

198
00:11:56,170 --> 00:11:58,660
他是希望你来劝我放弃
So, he's hoping you'll convince me to let it go.

199
00:11:58,660 --> 00:12:00,950
我能挣得比你给的多得多
Look, I'd make a killing compared to what you've paid me,

200
00:12:00,950 --> 00:12:03,690
但我们谈过要青史留名
but you and I talked about making a real mark.

201
00:12:12,890 --> 00:12:15,090
我父亲真的很喜欢弗兰西斯
My father really liked Francis.

202
00:12:16,780 --> 00:12:19,270
但作为我父亲  我们结婚前一天  他跟我说
But as my daddy, he said to me, the day before we got married,

203
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:21,140
"你只有一次人生  克莱尔
"You have one life, Claire.

204
00:12:22,170 --> 00:12:25,060
你确定你要跟这个男人共度此生吗"
Are you sure this is the man you wanna spend it with?"

205
00:12:25,330 --> 00:12:26,520
你怎么说的
What did you say?

206
00:12:27,550 --> 00:12:30,060
我说我不想在怀疑中度过人生
I said I didn't want to live my life full of doubts.

207
00:12:30,540 --> 00:12:33,510
我觉得弗兰西斯想让我怀疑自己
Well, I think Francis wants me to doubt myself.

208
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:39,070
-怎么回事  -我母亲  杀蜥蜴呢
- What was that? - My mother... killing a lizard.

209
00:12:45,230 --> 00:12:51,950
{\an8}在相当长的一段时间里

210
00:12:52,890 --> 00:12:56,070
-我给您开门  夫人  -我自己能开
- I'll get the door for you, ma'am. - I can open the door myself.

211
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,990
小心脚下  地上有血
Watch your step. There's blood on the floor.

212
00:13:18,550 --> 00:13:21,690
我要你亲自把这个交给总统
I want you to take this to the president, in person.

213
00:13:22,090 --> 00:13:25,380
-如果可以  今晚飞过去  -当然
- Try to get on a plane tonight if you can. - Of course.

214
00:13:37,580 --> 00:13:38,760
这是给你的
This one's for you.

215
00:13:41,190 --> 00:13:44,040
-是温的  -至少是免费的
- It's warm. - At least it's free.

216
00:13:46,970 --> 00:13:48,900
我或许得要你们兑现保险了
I may need to cash in my insurance.

217
00:13:50,380 --> 00:13:51,590
怎么了
What's going on?

218
00:13:52,710 --> 00:13:56,690
如果她拿下提名  我会得到什么位置
Tell me what my position would be if she wins the nomination.

219
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,400
是司法部长吗
Is it the attorney general?

220
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:02,990
-什么  -算了
- The what? - Never mind.

221
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,430
做竞选伙伴
For running mate?

222
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:07,280
现在考虑竞选伙伴太早了  他还没赢呢
It's way too early for running mates. He hasn't even won.

223
00:14:08,060 --> 00:14:10,880
-我们说的是一件事吗  -你先说
- Are we talking about the same thing? - You go first.

224
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:12,760
事不是那么办的
It doesn't work that way.

225
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:14,350
是你想找工作
Well, you're the one looking for a job.

226
00:14:14,350 --> 00:14:15,650
你要么告诉我
You can either involve me,

227
00:14:15,650 --> 00:14:16,330
要么就等着
or you can start reading

228
00:14:16,330 --> 00:14:18,760
报纸头条报道邓巴泄露婚姻消息
headlines about Dunbar pushing a marriage story.

229
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:21,130
那会害死你的
That would blow you up.

230
00:14:21,770 --> 00:14:24,760
道格已经起疑了  我没什么可怕的
Doug's already suspicious. I've got nothing to lose.

231
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:26,310
怎么样
So which is it?

232
00:14:28,010 --> 00:14:29,370
卢卡斯·古德温
Lucas Goodwin.

233
00:14:31,010 --> 00:14:33,420
他是《先驱报》的编辑  是那个...
He was an editor... at The Herald, the one who--

234
00:14:33,420 --> 00:14:36,010
-我们跟他谈过  -他不是在蹲监狱吗
- We spoke to him. - Isn't he in prison?

235
00:14:36,550 --> 00:14:37,940
出来了
Not anymore.

236
00:14:43,970 --> 00:14:46,760
他将于9:30出发
He's scheduled to depart at 0930 hours.

237
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,320
破晓前不久就能到塔林
That'll put him in Tallinn shortly before dawn.

238
00:14:49,540 --> 00:14:52,470
我们的站长与去萨拉马的护送队在待命了
Our station chief is standing by with the escort to Saaremaa.

239
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:54,110
这是行政命令
This is the executive order.

240
00:14:56,460 --> 00:14:58,530
-长官  -凯茜  我已经决定了
- Sir-- - Cathy, I've made my decision.

241
00:14:58,530 --> 00:15:00,750
-他到达后每小时报告一次  -是  先生
- Hourly updates once he lands. - Yes, sir.

242
00:15:02,050 --> 00:15:03,490
非常感谢
Thank you all very much.

243
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,410
告诉道格我准备好了
Tell Doug I'm ready.

244
00:15:13,590 --> 00:15:15,200
请坐吧  莉安
Please, have a seat, LeAnn.

245
00:15:18,130 --> 00:15:20,370
我很高兴你同意加入了
I'm delighted you've agreed to come on board.

246
00:15:20,460 --> 00:15:22,570
据我所知是有条件的
It's my understanding there is a condition attached.

247
00:15:22,570 --> 00:15:24,070
是的
Well, yes.

248
00:15:24,080 --> 00:15:27,630
她明白这个条件吧  你跟她谈过了
And she understands that condition? You've spoken with her?

249
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:29,660
抱歉  先生  我没说清楚
Oh, my apologies, sir. I wasn't clear.

250
00:15:29,660 --> 00:15:32,030
我是指我们的条件  不是你们的
I meant our condition, not yours.

251
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:54,850
在初选日
On Super Tuesday.

252
00:15:58,870 --> 00:16:01,360
这么大老远亲自送来啊
It's a long trip to deliver this in person.

253
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:02,820
这种东西
Well, it's not the sort of thing 

254
00:16:02,820 --> 00:16:04,990
可不能落入旁人手中
you'd want to end up in the wrong hands.

255
00:16:09,380 --> 00:16:11,490
你要留在华盛顿吗
Are you staying here in Washington?

256
00:16:11,540 --> 00:16:13,500
不  我马上回去
No, I'm going straight back.

257
00:16:14,330 --> 00:16:16,580
有什么话需要我带给第一夫人吗
Is there anything you'd like me to tell the First Lady?

258
00:16:16,830 --> 00:16:19,120
告诉她今晚就能回复她
Tell her she'll have her answer by this evening.

259
00:16:19,630 --> 00:16:23,350
-谢谢  总统先生  -一路顺风  哈维小姐
- Thank you, Mr. President. - Have a safe trip back, Ms. Harvey.

260
00:16:25,870 --> 00:16:27,310
我自己出去吧
I'll show myself out.

261
00:16:34,570 --> 00:16:37,500
在相当长的一段时间里  我和总统已经渐渐疏远
For quite some time, the president and I have been growing apart.

262
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,050
让密查姆进来
Have Meechum step in here.

263
00:16:39,050 --> 00:16:41,010
我们曾企图挽救我们的婚姻
We've attempted to save our marriage,

264
00:16:41,010 --> 00:16:43,840
但虽经过很多努力  我最终认识到
but after great effort, I've come to the conclusion

265
00:16:43,850 --> 00:16:45,580
我们的婚姻已不可挽救
that it can't be saved.

266
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:48,760
我今天很遗憾地宣布
It is with great regret that I announce today

267
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:51,100
我将申请离婚
I'm filing for divorce.

268
00:16:51,420 --> 00:16:54,550
-我们得阻止她  -在她到机场之前吗
- We have to stop her. - Before she gets to the airport?

269
00:16:54,550 --> 00:16:56,320
不是  克莱尔
No, I mean Claire.

270
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,550
您找我  先生
You asked for me, sir?

271
00:16:59,860 --> 00:17:01,080
进来
Come in.

272
00:17:07,590 --> 00:17:09,030
手机和固话...
Both the cell and the landline--

273
00:17:09,030 --> 00:17:11,330
我们进入了封锁  夫人  我们屏蔽了...
We're on lockdown, ma'am. We had to scramble all the--

274
00:17:11,330 --> 00:17:13,170
封锁  你在说什么呢
Lockdown? What are you talking about?

275
00:17:13,220 --> 00:17:14,890
请您待在房内
I'm gonna need you to stay in the house.

276
00:17:15,130 --> 00:17:16,790
-什么  -抱歉  夫人
- What-- - I'm sorry, ma'am.

277
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:19,250
你不能强迫我留在屋内
You can't force me to stay in here.

278
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:21,640
现在有针对您很可信的威胁...
There is a current, highly credible threat to your life--

279
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,960
我要跟你的上级说话
I need to speak to your supervising--

280
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:25,790
我是您在达拉斯的保安主管  夫人
I am the head of your detail here in Dallas, ma'am,

281
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:28,350
我得到命令要保护您安全留在屋内
and I've been ordered to keep you securely in this house.

282
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:58,090
{\an8}安德伍德2016

283
00:18:00,670 --> 00:18:02,000
安德伍德加油
Go Underwood!

284
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:11,720
-听啊  -笨蛋伍德  笨蛋伍德
- Listen. - Blunderwood! Blunderwood!

285
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:15,320
知道他们喊什么吗  "笨蛋伍德"
Do you know what they're chanting? "Blunderwood."

286
00:18:16,890 --> 00:18:18,340
如果我是他们的英语教授
And if I were their English professor,

287
00:18:18,340 --> 00:18:20,780
我会给他们的小聪明打A
why, I would give them all an "A" for cleverness...

288
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,270
但准确性打D
...but a "D" for accuracy.

289
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:27,780
但做总统就是如此
But that's part of being president.

290
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,630
会树敌
You make enemies,

291
00:18:29,820 --> 00:18:32,880
大家此刻就能听到我的一些敌人在外面呐喊
and you can hear some of mine just outside, right now.

292
00:18:33,590 --> 00:18:35,650
所以我很感激你们每个人
So, I am grateful to each and every one of you

293
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:37,590
今天前来表示对我的支持
for coming out and showing your support today.

294
00:18:37,590 --> 00:18:40,520
因为你们  我们能拿到提名
It's because of you we will win this nomination,

295
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:43,230
所以我今天来你们大学
and that's why I came to your college today.

296
00:18:49,820 --> 00:18:51,200
当然了  我知道
Now, of course, I knew

297
00:18:51,210 --> 00:18:53,600
今天会有抗议者来
that there would be protesters here today...

298
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:56,230
我本可以不来
and I could've chosen not to come,

299
00:18:56,370 --> 00:18:59,380
也可以选择离开时避开他们
or I could choose to avoid them as I leave,

300
00:18:59,380 --> 00:19:00,440
但我不打算那么做
but I'm not going to do that,

301
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:03,740
因为外面那些学生  你们的同学
because those students out there, your fellow classmates,

302
00:19:04,010 --> 00:19:05,720
我也是他们的总统
I'm their president, too.

303
00:19:05,980 --> 00:19:10,640
不管他们是不是为我投票  我也得带领他们
And whether they vote for me or not, I have to lead them as well.

304
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:14,150
所以  一定得倾听他们  跟他们说话
So, it's important to hear them, to talk to them,

305
00:19:14,780 --> 00:19:16,460
听他们的想法
to listen to their ideas,

306
00:19:16,460 --> 00:19:19,040
因为就像你们在大学学习
because, just as you're learning in college,

307
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:22,910
思想的多样化让我们都更加明智
a diversity of ideas makes us all wiser,

308
00:19:23,020 --> 00:19:26,140
对你们的总统来说也是如此
and that holds true even for your president.

309
00:19:26,270 --> 00:19:27,310
真正的领导
True leadership 

310
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:30,470
不是逃避与你意见相左的人
is not running away from those who disagree with you,

311
00:19:30,580 --> 00:19:31,940
而是要接纳他们
but embracing them,

312
00:19:31,940 --> 00:19:34,290
今天结束后  我就打算这么做
and that is exactly what I intend to do when I'm done today.

313
00:19:34,290 --> 00:19:36,950
我要出去接纳那群人
I'm gonna go out and embrace that entire crowd.

314
00:19:49,860 --> 00:19:51,910
我们不该坐军用飞机吗
Shouldn't we be taking a military plane?

315
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:53,180
那会吸引注意
That would draw attention.

316
00:19:53,810 --> 00:19:54,840
放松
Relax.

317
00:19:54,840 --> 00:19:56,890
一切都安排好了  你不会有事的
Everything's been worked out. You're in good hands.

318
00:19:58,910 --> 00:20:01,420
给  睡会儿吧
Here, get some sleep.

319
00:20:02,430 --> 00:20:04,210
今晚要走很久
It's gonna be a long trip tonight.

320
00:20:17,860 --> 00:20:20,980
笨蛋伍德  笨蛋伍德
Blunderwood! Blunderwood!

321
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,800
-有消息吗  -都安排好了  先生
- Any news? - Everything's secure, sir.

322
00:20:24,420 --> 00:20:25,930
我们爱你  安德伍德
We love you, Underwood! 

323
00:20:28,610 --> 00:20:29,840
感谢大家前来
Thank you all for coming out,

324
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:32,330
包括那些不完全支持我的人
even those of you who don't entirely support me.

325
00:20:32,330 --> 00:20:35,240
-总统你真棒  -谢谢
- Way to go, Mr. President! - Thank you.

326
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:39,270
我想尽量听听你们究竟反对我什么
I wanna try to hear what it is that you disagree with me about.

327
00:20:39,270 --> 00:20:41,390
我知道不是每个人都支持我
I understand not everyone's for me.

328
00:20:41,950 --> 00:20:44,730
-停止战争  -滚回加夫尼去吧
- No more wars! - Go back to Gaffney!

329
00:20:45,910 --> 00:20:47,930
你好吗  谢谢你能来
Hello, how are you? Thank you for coming out.

330
00:20:47,940 --> 00:20:49,140
你好  谢谢你能来
Hello, thank you for coming out.

331
00:20:49,150 --> 00:20:51,610
-你很棒  -我们知道你的真实面目
- You're doing a great job! - We know what you are!

332
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:53,060
你好
Hello.

333
00:20:54,210 --> 00:20:56,520
好了  我来是想听听你们的声音
All right, I'm here to try to listen to you,

334
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:59,360
但是一个一个说可能会比较好
but probably one at a time is gonna be a little better.

335
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:02,620
也许我们应该进行一对一的对话
Okay, maybe we could have a conversation, more one-on-one.

336
00:21:02,620 --> 00:21:04,060
这样很难听清
It's difficult to hear you.

337
00:21:04,220 --> 00:21:07,060
我知道你们不喜欢什么  但你们支持什么呢
I understand what you don't believe in, but what are you for?

338
00:21:07,090 --> 00:21:08,770
这样问也许比较好  你怎么样
That would be a good question. All right, how about you?

339
00:21:08,770 --> 00:21:10,580
你已经冲我喊了有一会儿了
You've been yelling at me for a little while.

340
00:21:10,580 --> 00:21:12,110
你觉得我该在哪些方面有所改变
What do you think I should be doing differently?

341
00:21:12,110 --> 00:21:13,400
-你应该辞职  -好吧
- You should resign. - Well, now,

342
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,980
我没在请求你们为我投票
I'm not asking for your vote,

343
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:16,960
但如果你是总统  你会怎么做呢
but what would you do if you were president?

344
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:18,710
你在毁掉我们的国家
You're ruining our country!

345
00:21:18,710 --> 00:21:21,090
我来这里是想听你们的心声
I came out here to try to listen to what you wanna say,

346
00:21:21,090 --> 00:21:22,530
但如果你们只是一直尖叫下去
but if all you're gonna do is scream--

347
00:21:22,530 --> 00:21:25,050
有枪
Gun!

348
00:21:32,690 --> 00:21:34,080
快走  快走
Let's go! Let's go!

349
00:21:34,210 --> 00:21:36,050
快走  快走  快快快
Move! Move! Go, go, go!

350
00:21:44,310 --> 00:21:48,300
有人企图刺杀总统
There has been an attempted assassination of the president.

351
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:50,820
弗兰克·安德伍德总统遭到了枪击
President Frank Underwood has been shot.

352
00:21:51,290 --> 00:22:01,290
{\an8}安德伍德总统遭枪击
哈蒙德大学发生刺杀未遂事件

353
00:21:51,410 --> 00:21:55,630
大约十分钟前发生于华盛顿特区
It occurred about ten minutes ago during a campaign event

354
00:21:55,770 --> 00:21:57,820
哈蒙德大学的一场竞选活动中
at Hammond University in Washington, D.C.

355
00:21:57,820 --> 00:22:02,360
我们尚不清楚总统的伤情
We do not yet know how severely the president has been wounded.

356
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:04,940
他正在被送往杰弗逊纪念医院
He is en route to Jefferson Memorial Hospital.

357
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:08,020
我们不知道他的情况有多严重
We don't know how serious his condition may be.

358
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:12,540
刺杀未遂事件的视频还没送到
Footage of the assassination attempt is still making its way to us,

359
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:14,840
但相信很快能够公布
and we expect to have that shortly.

360
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:16,660
目击者声称
Witnesses are reporting

361
00:22:16,660 --> 00:22:19,140
当时有连续好几声枪响
that there was a quick succession of gunshots,

362
00:22:19,140 --> 00:22:20,450
约有四五发
four or five,

363
00:22:20,550 --> 00:22:24,170
枪手是一个人  身份还未确认
a lone gunman whose identity we are still trying to determine.

364
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:26,640
已得知枪手已被击毙
We've been told the gunman was killed,

365
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:28,810
另有至少一名特勤人员遇难
as well as at least one Secret Service agent,

366
00:22:28,810 --> 00:22:32,580
但我们还未得到明确证实
but we don't have definitive confirmation of that yet.

367
00:22:32,580 --> 00:22:36,690
我们也不清楚枪手和特勤人员的身份
We don't yet know who the gunman may be or who the agent is.

368
00:22:36,690 --> 00:22:38,820
-怎么了  -总统遇刺了
- What's happened? - The president's been shot.

369
00:22:39,820 --> 00:22:41,340
导播现在告诉我
I'm hearing now that the president

370
00:22:41,340 --> 00:22:44,920
总统至少腹部中了一枪  也许不止
received at least one gunshot to the abdomen, possibly more,

371
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,040
他紧捂腹部
that he clutched his stomach,

372
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:48,330
立即倒地
that he fell instantly to the ground,

373
00:22:48,340 --> 00:22:50,280
现场尖叫连连  人群陷入恐慌
and there were screams, people panicking,

374
00:22:50,280 --> 00:22:52,950
场面十分混乱
that it has been very chaotic at that scene.

375
00:22:53,190 --> 00:22:55,250
目前我们获得的消息很有限
We have very little information at this time,

376
00:22:55,250 --> 00:22:58,040
仅知道总统遭遇枪击受伤
other than shots were fired, the president wounded.

377
00:22:58,260 --> 00:23:00,260
但如我所言  他还活着
But as I say, he is alive.

378
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:02,040
我们也还没得到
We've gotten no official

379
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:04,060
白宫的官方声明
statement from the White House as of yet,

380
00:23:04,060 --> 00:23:06,160
不了解总统的具体情况
either the president's precise condition

381
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:09,170
或是布莱斯副总统的行踪
or the whereabouts of Vice President Blythe.

382
00:23:09,170 --> 00:23:12,830
有消息称他目前正在白宫  但我们还不能确认
He is believed to be at the White House. We cannot confirm that,

383
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:16,410
我们也不清楚他是否会出任代总统
nor do we know if he will take over as acting president,

384
00:23:16,410 --> 00:23:18,180
履行宪法第25条修正案
assuming the duties of the presidency

385
00:23:18,180 --> 00:23:21,790
规定的总统职责
under the terms of the 25th Amendment to the Constitution.

386
00:23:22,030 --> 00:23:23,870
但如果总统的伤势
That would seem likely, however,

387
00:23:23,870 --> 00:23:26,380
如我们认为的那样严重
if the president's wounds are as serious 

388
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:28,180
这将很有可能
as we believe them to be.

389
00:23:29,060 --> 00:23:31,220
这是国家的艰难时刻
This is a difficult moment for the country.

390
00:23:31,290 --> 00:23:34,010
这不是我国总统第一次遇刺
It is not the first time that a president has been shot

391
00:23:34,030 --> 00:23:36,840
我和很多人此前都曾经历过
in my lifetime or in many of yours.

392
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:40,320
但即便是那些经历过这种事的人
But even for those of us who have experienced this before,

393
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:44,150
此事仍触目惊心  骇人听闻
it is no less of a shock, it is no less terrifying.

394
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:47,940
这是检验我国坚韧的时刻
It is the moment when our nation's resilience,

395
00:23:47,940 --> 00:23:49,520
检验人民团结的时刻
when our collective strength,

396
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:53,090
最能检验一切的时刻
the moment when all of that is tested the most.

397
00:23:53,470 --> 00:23:54,630
我们难以想象
And we can only imagine

398
00:23:54,630 --> 00:23:57,550
第一夫人此时多么痛苦
how difficult it must be for the First Lady.

399
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:06,420
-弗兰西斯他...  -迈克尔说了
- Francis-- - Michael told me.

400
00:24:11,580 --> 00:24:13,250
我得回华盛顿
I have to go back to Washington.

401
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:16,760
那你还耽搁什么
Well, what are you waiting for?

402
00:24:20,820 --> 00:24:23,290
还指望我安慰你吗
Do you expect me to console you?

403
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:26,190
不  我只是...
No, I just...

404
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:30,280
-再见  母亲  -克莱尔
- Goodbye, Mother. - Claire.

405
00:24:32,220 --> 00:24:33,900
我希望他死
I hope he dies.

406
00:24:42,360 --> 00:24:46,230
克莱尔  我无法想象你多么难过
Claire, I can't imagine how difficult this must be.

407
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:47,730
需要我帮忙吗
Is there anything I can do?

408
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:49,770
谢谢你来电慰问  副总统先生
I appreciate the call, Mr. Vice President,

409
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:52,350
但你目前肯定还有许多事得处理
but I'm sure you've got a lot to take care of right now.

410
00:24:52,350 --> 00:24:54,310
你需要我的帮助吗
Is there anything I can do to help you?

411
00:24:54,310 --> 00:24:55,760
一旦我们弄清
I'll be making a brief appearance

412
00:24:55,760 --> 00:25:00,260
目前的状况  我就会进行简短发言
once we have a better sense of... where things stand.

413
00:25:00,520 --> 00:25:01,940
需要我在场吗
Would you like me to be there?

414
00:25:02,150 --> 00:25:05,520
这样最好  让国家见到第一夫人
I think it would be good, the country seeing the First Lady.

415
00:25:06,380 --> 00:25:09,420
我觉得让他们见到你临危不乱更重要
I think it's more important that they see your steady hand.

416
00:25:09,420 --> 00:25:12,850
如果你在我身边  我会更有底气
If you're by my side, it would certainly make it steadier.

417
00:25:13,140 --> 00:25:15,070
当然  我都听你的
Of course. Anything you ask.

418
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:18,990
我会为你们祈祷  为你们俩
I'm gonna be praying for you. For both of you.

419
00:25:20,020 --> 00:25:21,340
谢谢  唐
Thank you, Don.

420
00:25:30,310 --> 00:25:31,530
好了
Okay.

421
00:25:42,510 --> 00:25:43,680
这边  先生
This way, sir.

422
00:26:02,100 --> 00:26:05,710
{\an8}总统  2014年10月30日

423
00:26:26,120 --> 00:26:27,210
谢谢  先生
Thank you, sir.

424
00:26:29,340 --> 00:26:30,140
有高度机密事务
The acting president needs

425
00:26:30,140 --> 00:26:32,310
需要向代总统报告
to be briefed on a highly classified matter.

426
00:26:32,720 --> 00:26:35,040
没有军事机密许可的人请离开房间
Everyone without military clearance, we'll need the room.

427
00:26:46,420 --> 00:26:48,160
枪手开了两枪
It was in fact two shots.

428
00:26:46,810 --> 00:26:56,810
{\an8}袭击者确认死亡
安德伍德在杰弗逊纪念医院

429
00:26:46,890 --> 00:26:56,890
{\an9}刺杀未遂事件

430
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:51,620
一枪擦伤了身体  就在右臂之下
One that grazed the torso just beneath the right arm

431
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:53,980
另一枪射入了腹部
and the second which entered the abdomen,

432
00:26:54,330 --> 00:26:55,810
多半伤了肝脏
possibly into his liver.

433
00:26:55,810 --> 00:26:59,090
显然是这一枪造成了最严重的伤害
Obviously, it was that shot that did the greatest damage.

434
00:26:59,290 --> 00:27:03,100
据悉  总统目前情况危急
The president is currently reported to be in critical condition.

435
00:27:03,670 --> 00:27:04,930
为保护总统遇害的
The Secret Service agent

436
00:27:04,930 --> 00:27:07,840
特勤局特工名叫艾德华·密查姆
that was killed protecting the president was Edward Meechum.

437
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:09,600
他是总统安保队队长
He is the head of the president's detail,

438
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,440
我们现在可以确定
and we can confirm that now.

439
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:14,400
他中枪后  在死前
After being shot and before he died,

440
00:27:14,760 --> 00:27:18,780
杀死了身份仍未知的袭击者
he killed the assailant whose identity is still unknown.

441
00:27:19,210 --> 00:27:21,340
我们正等待白宫新闻发言人赛斯·格雷森的
We're waiting now on a press conference from the White House

442
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:22,820
新闻发布会
from Press Secretary Seth Grayson,

443
00:27:22,820 --> 00:27:26,590
发布会稍后就会举行
and we expect to have that beginning in just a few moments.

444
00:27:27,450 --> 00:27:30,850
先给我看过两遍  再对外确认
We confirm nothing unless you run it past me twice first,

445
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:31,980
-我不希望...  -格雷森先生...
- I don't want-- - Mr. Grayson...

446
00:27:31,980 --> 00:27:35,240
马上过去  不要有任何传言  只要事实
I'm on my way. We don't want any rumors, only facts.

447
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:36,920
一名学生宣称是特勤局的人
There's a student who's claiming it was the Secret Service

448
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:39,120
-开的第一枪  -我刚说了什么
- who fired the first shot. - What did I just say?

449
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:41,650
-别拿这种屁话浪费我时间  -先生
- Do not waste my time with that bullshit. - Sir,

450
00:27:41,820 --> 00:27:42,530
媒体在等了
the press is waiting.

451
00:27:42,530 --> 00:27:44,600
行  我马上过去  我的...
All right, I'm... I'm coming. Uh, where's my...

452
00:27:50,710 --> 00:27:53,890
今日午后12点38分  副总统唐纳德·布莱斯
At 12:38 this afternoon, Vice President Donald Blythe

453
00:27:53,890 --> 00:27:56,370
由内阁任命为代总统
was authorized as acting president by the cabinet.

454
00:27:56,500 --> 00:27:58,130
目前他正与内阁会面
He is currently meeting with them.

455
00:27:58,560 --> 00:28:01,800
约20分钟前  第一夫人在安德鲁空军基地降落
Approximately 20 minutes ago, the First Lady landed at Andrews.

456
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:04,510
她不久就会达到医院
She is expected to arrive at the hospital shortly.

457
00:28:09,110 --> 00:28:11,600
-安德伍德夫人  -他怎么样
- Mrs. Underwood. - How is he?

458
00:28:11,940 --> 00:28:14,720
他们还在手术室里  大概还得要几小时
They're still in the OR. Probably a few hours left to go.

459
00:28:16,550 --> 00:28:17,960
他能保住命吗
Is he going to live?

460
00:28:18,540 --> 00:28:21,830
他被直接击中肝脏  肝脏部分破裂
He took a direct hit to his liver, which is partially shattered.

461
00:28:21,830 --> 00:28:25,510
幸运的是  左叶有一部分几乎完好无损
Fortunately, part of the left lobe is mostly intact.

462
00:28:26,940 --> 00:28:29,800
我们认为  他有很大几率挺过手术
Now, we think there's a decent chance he will survive surgery,

463
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:33,830
但即便如此  真正的难关在术后才开始
but even if he does, that's when the real fight begins.

464
00:28:34,700 --> 00:28:36,240
我想见他
I'd like to see him.

465
00:28:36,460 --> 00:28:39,060
他一结束我就告诉您
As soon as he's out, I'll make sure you know.

466
00:28:39,130 --> 00:28:40,380
好  谢谢
Okay, thank you.

467
00:29:01,870 --> 00:29:04,620
我建议取消这次行动
I'd recommend we call off this operation,

468
00:29:04,620 --> 00:29:06,350
现在就让飞机调头
we turn the plane around now.

469
00:29:06,350 --> 00:29:08,440
我不同意  我们精心计划过了
I disagree. It's well planned.

470
00:29:08,440 --> 00:29:09,690
而且总统已经签字了
The president already signed off.

471
00:29:09,690 --> 00:29:11,540
总统可能撑不过去
The president might die.

472
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:15,490
-国务卿女士  -不准这样说  凯茜
- Madam Secretary... - We'll have no talk like that, Cathy.

473
00:29:16,420 --> 00:29:17,730
抱歉  先生
My apologies, sir.

474
00:29:17,730 --> 00:29:19,880
我想说的是
What I am trying to say is that 

475
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:23,010
针锋相对的风险太大了
it is too risky to antagonize--

476
00:29:23,170 --> 00:29:24,680
我们的目的是吓唬他们  不是
The point was to scare them, not--

477
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:26,140
在最高指挥官
To do anything of this nature

478
00:29:26,140 --> 00:29:28,740
无法工作时做这种事情
while the commander in chief is incapacitated,

479
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:30,680
-俄国人会利用这时机  -我们现在高度警戒
- the Russians will take advantage-- - We're at high alert.

480
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:32,550
我们准备好面对一切不测了
We're prepared for all eventualities.

481
00:29:31,290 --> 00:29:34,420
{\an8}不能把军队当成故障保险
We don't want the military to be the fail-safe here.

482
00:29:34,420 --> 00:29:37,650
副...总统先生
Mr. Vice... Mr. President...

483
00:29:38,750 --> 00:29:40,350
我认为  执行总统签署的命令
I believe it is our duty to carry out the orders

484
00:29:40,350 --> 00:29:41,910
是我们的职责
that the president signed.

485
00:29:41,910 --> 00:29:45,990
-情况已经变了  -计划依然可行
- The circumstances have changed. - The plan is sound.

486
00:29:48,090 --> 00:29:48,910
您想让我怎么办  先生
So, what would you like to do, sir,

487
00:29:48,910 --> 00:29:50,900
继续还是终止任务
continue the mission or abort?

488
00:29:53,390 --> 00:29:56,080
我想再考虑考虑
Uh, I... I wanna think on it.

489
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:57,510
按计划他将在两小时后降落
He's scheduled to land in two hours.

490
00:29:57,510 --> 00:29:58,730
我只想
I just want...

491
00:30:00,130 --> 00:30:02,870
我得考虑一下  我们休息一下吧
I've gotta think. Let's take a break.

492
00:30:02,870 --> 00:30:05,620
我得整理整理思绪
I, uh, I need to process all this.

493
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:16,860
先生
Sir?

494
00:30:19,790 --> 00:30:20,640
总统权衡过一切
The president weighed everything--

495
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:22,570
凯茜说得很有道理
Cathy brought up some good points.

496
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:24,530
她从最开始就反对这件事
She's been against this from the very beginning,

497
00:30:24,530 --> 00:30:25,340
但总统明确
but the president clearly--

498
00:30:25,340 --> 00:30:27,630
给我点时间  道格  求你了
Just give me some time, Doug, please?

499
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:30,320
在我耳边吼的人太多了
I've got too many people barking in my ear.

500
00:30:40,530 --> 00:30:42,200
总统已经做完手术
The president is out of surgery,

501
00:30:42,990 --> 00:30:45,820
他病情稳定但依然危重
and he is in stable but critical condition.

502
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:51,780
听我说  听我说  我们要有序得来
Excuse me! Excuse me! We are going to keep this orderly.

503
00:30:51,780 --> 00:30:53,650
先让萨克逊医生发表完声明
Dr. Saxon will finish his statement,

504
00:30:53,650 --> 00:30:56,080
然后我们再回答你们的问题  谢谢
and then we'll answer your questions. Thank you.

505
00:30:56,080 --> 00:30:58,750
手术进行了6小时28分钟
The surgery lasted six hours, 28 minutes.

506
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:00,840
切除了四分之三的肝脏
Three quarters of his liver was removed.

507
00:31:01,090 --> 00:31:03,300
肝脏  哪怕只剩四分之一
A liver, even one quarter of a liver,

508
00:31:03,300 --> 00:31:07,060
都有能力在六至八周内再生
has the ability to regenerate within six to eight weeks.

509
00:31:07,060 --> 00:31:09,910
我们每小时都会对他进行血检
We will be conducting blood tests every hour.

510
00:31:09,910 --> 00:31:11,980
监测肝酶水平  血氨水平  凝血酶原时间
Enzymes, ammonia levels, PT times,

511
00:31:11,980 --> 00:31:14,410
这些在声明单上都有说明
I believe these are all explained in the handout.

512
00:31:14,210 --> 00:31:24,210
{\an9}《华盛顿先驱报》提供照片

513
00:31:14,420 --> 00:31:16,340
...医学报告  我们马上就继续
...the medical report, live from the White House,

514
00:31:16,350 --> 00:31:18,370
白宫的现场直播
which we will return to shortly.

515
00:31:18,380 --> 00:31:20,180
但我们在密切关注一则重大新闻
But we have breaking news we're following.

516
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:23,010
在之前的报道中  刺客被认为是
The would-be assassin was previously reported

517
00:31:23,010 --> 00:31:25,920
俄亥俄州代顿的约翰·卡莱尔
as John Carlyle from Dayton, Ohio,

518
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:28,350
但现在司法部的消息源称
but sources in the Department of Justice now say 

519
00:31:28,350 --> 00:31:31,590
这其实是卢卡斯·古德温的化名
this was actually an alias for Lucas Goodwin,

520
00:31:31,710 --> 00:31:33,440
他曾是《华盛顿先驱报》的编辑
a former editor at The Washington Herald

521
00:31:33,440 --> 00:31:37,520
两年前被判犯下了网络恐怖主义罪
who was convicted of cyberterrorism nearly two years ago.

522
00:31:37,650 --> 00:31:41,270
如果我们暂停这段手机拍摄的枪击视频
Now, if we freeze this cell phone footage of the shooting

523
00:31:41,290 --> 00:31:45,050
然后将枪手的脸与古德温的照片进行的对比
and we compare the shooter's face to this picture of Goodwin...

524
00:31:44,290 --> 00:31:47,690
{\an7}目击者录像

525
00:31:45,580 --> 00:31:48,030
比照惊人
well, the comparison is striking

526
00:31:48,110 --> 00:31:49,350
似乎也证实了
and would seem to confirm

527
00:31:49,350 --> 00:31:52,460
来自司法部消息源的说法
what we're hearing from our sources in the DOJ,

528
00:31:52,550 --> 00:31:54,880
即古德温已于近日获释
who say Goodwin was recently released

529
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:57,400
并加入了证人保护计划
and is in a witness protection program.

530
00:31:58,620 --> 00:32:00,370
感觉好怪  想到我...
It's so strange to think that I--

531
00:32:01,170 --> 00:32:04,200
多久  那就是两小时前吧  还不到
It was, what? Just two hours before? Less than.

532
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,840
他是什么反应
How did he react?

533
00:32:07,230 --> 00:32:10,340
他很冷漠吧  我看不透他
He was cold, I guess. I couldn't really read him.

534
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:13,580
他看起来好虚弱
He looks so weak.

535
00:32:14,810 --> 00:32:16,490
我应该回华盛顿吗
Should I come back to Washington?

536
00:32:16,910 --> 00:32:19,010
看看接下来几天的情况吧
Let's see how the next couple of days go.

537
00:32:20,120 --> 00:32:21,920
随时通知我  我立马上飞机
Well, just say the word, I'm on a plane.

538
00:32:23,170 --> 00:32:25,610
好吧  谢谢  莉安  晚安
All right, thank you, LeAnn. Good night.

539
00:32:25,610 --> 00:32:26,790
晚安
Good night.

540
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:34,390
弗兰西斯  能听到吗
Francis, can you hear me?

541
00:32:43,690 --> 00:32:44,950
弗兰西斯
Francis.

542
00:32:50,990 --> 00:32:52,870
我刚跟艾迪的父母谈了  夫人
I just spoke to Eddie's parents, ma'am.

543
00:32:53,380 --> 00:32:54,830
您说您想给他们打电话
You said you wanted to call them?

544
00:32:55,540 --> 00:32:56,900
是的  谢谢
Yes, thank you.

545
00:33:01,150 --> 00:33:03,450
艾德华不止是位英雄  密查姆太太
Edward was more than a hero, Mrs. Meechum. 

546
00:33:03,450 --> 00:33:04,730
他是我们的朋友
He was our friend.

547
00:33:05,870 --> 00:33:07,810
我非常遗憾您失去了儿子
I'm so sorry for your loss.

548
00:33:10,670 --> 00:33:12,770
如果有什么我能为您
Please, let me know if there's anything

549
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:15,120
和您的家人做的  务必告诉我
I can do for you and your family.

550
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:16,690
您随时可以给我打电话
You can call me anytime.

551
00:33:18,380 --> 00:33:20,380
是的  太太  这是我的私人号码
Yes, ma'am, that is my private number. 

552
00:33:20,670 --> 00:33:22,560
我再次深表遗憾
And again, I'm so sorry.

553
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:33,730
-卢卡斯·古德温  -我们不知道他出狱了
- Lucas Goodwin? - We didn't know he was out.

554
00:33:33,730 --> 00:33:35,970
怎么可能  他被释放了你却不知道
How can that happen? He's released and you didn't know--

555
00:33:35,970 --> 00:33:38,300
夫人  说到威胁
Ma'am... as far as threats go,

556
00:33:38,300 --> 00:33:40,500
我们最近几乎都在忙着应付您
we've been far more occupied with you lately.

557
00:33:43,420 --> 00:33:46,030
我希望我们能合作  因为我需要您的帮助
I'm hoping that we can work together, because I need your help.

558
00:33:47,540 --> 00:33:50,210
-怎么帮  -副总统
- How? - The vice president.

559
00:33:50,710 --> 00:33:53,050
我们谈过了  我告诉他我会陪他出面
We spoke. I told him I would appear with him.

560
00:33:53,050 --> 00:33:54,390
不是声明的事
Not the statement.

561
00:33:55,210 --> 00:33:57,080
他现在有个决定难以定夺
He's having trouble making a decision.

562
00:33:58,020 --> 00:33:59,640
您能跟我一起回白宫吗
Can you come back to the White House with me?

563
00:34:02,220 --> 00:34:03,410
这事很严重  夫人
It's serious, ma'am. 

564
00:34:03,930 --> 00:34:05,440
我可以在路上跟您说明情况
I can fill you in on the way.

565
00:34:10,410 --> 00:34:11,810
我去拿我的东西
I'll grab my things.

566
00:34:22,180 --> 00:34:23,890
我不能让你进去  先生
I can't let you go any farther, sir. 

567
00:34:24,100 --> 00:34:25,510
我是他的幕僚长
I'm his Chief of Staff.

568
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:26,920
抱歉  先生 
I'm sorry, sir. 

569
00:34:27,320 --> 00:34:29,360
现在只有医生和第一夫人可以进去
Only doctors and the First Lady for now.

570
00:34:53,590 --> 00:34:54,780
克莱尔
Claire.

571
00:34:55,910 --> 00:34:57,110
你好
Hello.

572
00:34:59,200 --> 00:35:00,410
你好吗
How are you?

573
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:02,280
-累坏了  -肯定的
- Exhausted. - I'm sure.

574
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,610
你也一定累坏了
You must be, too.

575
00:35:04,050 --> 00:35:08,070
有太多东西我不了解  快把我...搞晕了
There's so much I don't know. It's... overwhelming.

576
00:35:08,260 --> 00:35:11,350
先生  我已向第一夫人说明了米尔金行动
Sir, I briefed the First Lady on the Milkin operation.

577
00:35:11,520 --> 00:35:12,640
考虑到她曾与俄国有过直接交涉
I thought she might have some insight,

578
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:14,930
我想也许她会有一些见解
given her experience working directly with Russia.

579
00:35:15,590 --> 00:35:18,820
我知道已经有很多人为你出谋划策了
I know you've had a lot of people weigh in already.

580
00:35:19,860 --> 00:35:23,040
我重视你的建议  克莱尔  我很高兴你能来
I value your input, Claire. I'm glad you're here.

581
00:35:24,480 --> 00:35:27,710
-道格拉斯  能让我们单独谈谈吗  -当然
- Douglas, will you give us a minute? - Of course.

582
00:35:28,210 --> 00:35:29,630
我会跟内阁在一起  先生
I'll be with the cabinet, sir.

583
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:33,430
你知道人们常说
You know that thing that people say,

584
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:35,660
上帝不会让你无法承受
"God never gives you more than you can handle"?

585
00:35:36,220 --> 00:35:37,360
知道
Yes.

586
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:39,790
我的玛乔莉  愿主保佑她
My Marjory, God bless her,

587
00:35:40,590 --> 00:35:42,350
她说那是屁话
she said that was pure bullshit.

588
00:35:45,700 --> 00:35:47,350
你丈夫正在与死神搏斗
Oh, listen to me complaining

589
00:35:47,840 --> 00:35:49,410
你还得听我抱怨
while your husband is fighting for his life.

590
00:35:49,410 --> 00:35:52,190
没关系  其实我需要分散下注意
Oh, it's okay. Actually, I need the distraction.

591
00:35:52,190 --> 00:35:53,390
我们谈谈俄国吧
Let's talk Russia.

592
00:35:54,130 --> 00:35:59,000
我很纠结  我们有架飞机在北海上空盘旋
I'm torn. Uh, we have this plane circling over the North Sea...

593
00:35:59,790 --> 00:36:02,730
-我不知道该怎么做  -你的直觉是什么
- and I don't know what to do. - Well, what does your gut tell you?

594
00:36:04,530 --> 00:36:06,730
我从来就不是靠直觉做事的人
I've never been a gut sort of guy.

595
00:36:07,610 --> 00:36:09,710
如果有把枪指在我头上...
I mean, if I had a gun to my head...

596
00:36:09,900 --> 00:36:14,630
-对不起  我比喻不当  - 没关系  继续
- Sorry, that was a poor choice of words. - It's fine. Go on.

597
00:36:16,660 --> 00:36:19,450
我理解总统希望达到什么
I understand what the president hoped to achieve,

598
00:36:19,450 --> 00:36:22,170
但一想到激怒俄国...
but the thought of provoking Russia...

599
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:27,430
我这才刚开始了解此事的复杂性
And I'm just beginning to immerse myself in all the complexities.

600
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:32,290
如果换了弗兰克  他会怎么做呢
What would Frank do, if he were in my shoes right now?

601
00:36:32,850 --> 00:36:34,280
如果他在这儿  他会告诉你
If he were here, he'd tell you

602
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:36,270
那是你最不应该考虑的事
that's the last thing you should think about,

603
00:36:36,270 --> 00:36:38,330
因为他不在这儿  你在
because he's not here, you are.

604
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:40,130
你会怎么做
What would you do?

605
00:36:40,830 --> 00:36:42,790
继续这项任务还是叫他回来
Proceed with the mission or bring him back?

606
00:36:44,910 --> 00:36:46,330
两者我都不喜欢
I don't like either.

607
00:36:47,380 --> 00:36:48,870
我只有这两个选择
Those are my options.

608
00:36:48,870 --> 00:36:52,250
如果说在弗兰西斯身边28年  我学到了什么
Well, if there's one thing I've learned, 28 years with Francis,

609
00:36:52,250 --> 00:36:54,090
那就是他重复多次的那句话
and he said it time and time again,

610
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:56,500
"如果你不喜欢餐具的摆放..."
"If you don't like the way the table is set..."

611
00:36:56,750 --> 00:36:59,310
-"那就掀桌子"  -没错
- "Then turn over the table." - That's right.

612
00:36:59,310 --> 00:37:01,100
他跟我说过不止一次
He's said it to me, more than once.

613
00:37:01,540 --> 00:37:03,320
那么你就应该这么做  唐纳德
Then that's what you should do, Donald.

614
00:37:05,360 --> 00:37:08,390
-但要怎么做呢  -我们一起想想吧
- But how? - Well, let's figure it out.

615
00:37:23,020 --> 00:37:25,080
我们不是早该降落了吗
Weren't we supposed to have landed already?

616
00:37:25,700 --> 00:37:28,570
-我们在待命航线上  -为什么  出什么事了吗
- We're in a holding pattern. - Why? Is something wrong?

617
00:37:29,100 --> 00:37:31,090
我只知道我们在待命航线上
All I know is we're in a holding pattern.

618
00:37:56,140 --> 00:37:57,200
道格
Doug.

619
00:37:58,140 --> 00:38:00,030
这架飞机很快就会没油
This plane's gonna run out of fuel soon.

620
00:38:00,030 --> 00:38:01,760
我们一定要找个地方让它降落
We're gonna have to put it down somewhere.

621
00:38:18,470 --> 00:38:21,430
我马上就发声明  先跟记者团打声招呼吧
I'll be making a statement shortly. Let's notify the press corps.

622
00:38:21,540 --> 00:38:25,230
-关于行动吗  -不  让美国人民放心
- About the operation? - No, to reassure the American people.

623
00:38:25,700 --> 00:38:27,480
-我在那边等你吗  -给我十分钟
- Shall I meet you in there? - Ten minutes. 

624
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:28,380
内阁怎么样
The cabinet?

625
00:38:28,610 --> 00:38:30,720
-还在等您的决定  先生  -很好
- Still waiting on your decision, sir. - Good.

626
00:38:30,830 --> 00:38:32,080
走吧
Let's go.

627
00:38:41,520 --> 00:38:43,480
把飞机降落在中国
I want you to land the plane in China.

628
00:38:44,350 --> 00:38:45,490
中国吗  先生
China, sir?

629
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:47,500
没有中国的钱就没有救市计划
There's no bailout without Chinese money.

630
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,960
我们把米尔金给他们  他们会有更多筹码
We give them Milkin, they have more leverage.

631
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:52,530
先生  那就放弃我们的筹码了
Sir, that gives away our leverage.

632
00:38:52,530 --> 00:38:54,150
我不赞成政权更迭  但那是...
I'm not for regime change, but that just...

633
00:38:54,150 --> 00:38:56,380
这是佩特罗夫最想不到的事
It's the last thing that Petrov is expecting.

634
00:38:56,940 --> 00:38:59,460
他们会要求东西伯利亚的钻井权
They'll demand drilling access in eastern Siberia.

635
00:38:59,460 --> 00:39:02,170
等他们提出  我们就是两害中较轻的那个
And when they do, we become the lesser of two evils.

636
00:39:02,190 --> 00:39:04,020
先生  总统从未打算
Sir, at no time did the president

637
00:39:04,020 --> 00:39:05,760
把中国搅进来...
intend on bringing China into the mix...

638
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:07,430
让飞机降落在中国领土上
Get the plane on Chinese soil.

639
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:10,060
并且移交米尔金的资产  这就是我的决定
And turn over Milkin's assets. That's my decision.

640
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:18,120
-我是向你求助的  -我也给予了帮助
- I asked for your help. - And that's what I gave.

641
00:39:18,120 --> 00:39:20,060
不  中国不在总统的计划范围内
No, China wasn't part of the president's plan.

642
00:39:20,070 --> 00:39:22,210
它在代总统的计划范围内
It's part of the acting president's plan.

643
00:39:22,420 --> 00:39:24,880
-你准备好了吗  -好了  就等你了
- You ready? - Yes, whenever you are.

644
00:39:25,330 --> 00:39:27,340
-赛斯  -是  先生
- Seth? - Yes, sir.

645
00:39:38,610 --> 00:39:41,630
女士们先生们  有请代总统
Ladies and gentlemen, the acting president.

646
00:39:46,140 --> 00:39:47,400
请坐
Please, sit.

647
00:39:49,310 --> 00:39:53,670
今天对所有美国民众来说都是艰难的一天
This is a difficult day for all Americans,

648
00:39:53,670 --> 00:39:55,820
特别是安德伍德夫人
particularly for Mrs. Underwood,

649
00:39:55,970 --> 00:39:58,230
很感谢她能来到这儿
who is gracious enough to be here,

650
00:39:58,900 --> 00:40:02,730
在我向焦虑的国民讲话时  给我力量
to lend me strength while I address an anxious nation.

651
00:40:02,730 --> 00:40:04,460
总统先生
Mr. President!

